ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this course to students with some background in economy who want to study optimization theory and some applications.
i found this class very interesting and intellectually satisfying. i would recommend it to anyone who likes mathematics and who wants to see some applications of mathematics.
I will definitely recommend this course to a fellow student. It is a truly useful and interesting course!

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Since this course covers introductory to advanced topics in optimization in general, it is useful for almost any applied engineering/science student. Since Ido mostly applied algorithms for signal processing, knowledge of optimization techniques is crucial.
The course taught me a lot!
